{"action":"created","issue":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/issues/1510","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/issues/1510/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/issues/1510/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/issues/1510/events","html_url":"https://github.com/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/issues/1510","id":1034034209,"node_id":"I_kwDOBEVPe849ohwh","number":1510,"title":"Error when using custom Wfact or Wfact_t in SplitODEProblem","user":{"login":"dennisYatunin","id":8855258,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjg4NTUyNTg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/8855258?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/dennisYatunin","html_url":"https://github.com/dennisYatunin","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dennisYatunin/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dennisYatunin/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dennisYatunin/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dennisYatunin/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dennisYatunin/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dennisYatunin/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dennisYatunin/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dennisYatunin/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dennisYatunin/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"open","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":4,"created_at":"2021-10-23T01:07:10Z","updated_at":"2022-04-09T15:35:56Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"In order to use a custom `Wfact` or `Wfact_t` with a split ODE solver, one needs to specify a problem of the form `SplitODEProblem(ODEFunction(f_implicit!; Wfact_t = custom_wfact_t!), f_explicit!, u0, tspan, p)`. [This results](https://github.com/SciML/SciMLBase.jl/blob/7f81097a492ab1707209530627a494bfb10c90c5/src/problems/ode_problems.jl#L186-L228) in an `ODEProblem` that contains a `SplitFunction` `f`, where the specified custom value of `Wfact_t` (or `Wfact`) is stored in `f.f1.Wfact_t`. The corresponding field in `f`, `f.Wfact_t`, contains its [default value](https://github.com/SciML/SciMLBase.jl/blob/7f81097a492ab1707209530627a494bfb10c90c5/src/scimlfunctions.jl#L533) of `nothing`.

In order to determine whether a custom `Wfact_t` has been provided, [`has_Wfact_t(f)`](https://github.com/SciML/SciMLBase.jl/blob/7f81097a492ab1707209530627a494bfb10c90c5/src/scimlfunctions.jl#L1324) checks `f.f1.Wfact_t`, rather than `f.Wfact_t`. When computing the value of `W`, `calc_W!` [checks if `has_Wfact_t(f)` when the solver requires `Wfact_t`](https://github.com/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/blob/3a9b6dc35e3ed19ddda4801cc5c791bf8771f956/src/derivative_utils.jl#L468) (or it [checks if  `has_Wfact(f)` when the solver requires `Wfact`](https://github.com/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/blob/3a9b6dc35e3ed19ddda4801cc5c791bf8771f956/src/derivative_utils.jl#L473)). If the problem is specified as above, this condition is satisfied. Unfortunately, on the following line, `calc_W!` calls [`f.Wfact_t(W, u, p, dtgamma, t)`](https://github.com/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/blob/3a9b6dc35e3ed19ddda4801cc5c791bf8771f956/src/derivative_utils.jl#L469) (or [`f.Wfact(W, u, p, dtgamma, t)`](https://github.com/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/blob/3a9b6dc35e3ed19ddda4801cc5c791bf8771f956/src/derivative_utils.jl#L474)). Since `f.Wfact_t` is `nothing` for a `SplitFunction`, this causes an error.

There is also another issue when the problem is specified as `SplitODEProblem(ODEFunction(f_implicit!; jac_prototype = CustomWRepresentation(), Wfact_t = custom_wfact_t!), f_explicit!, u0, tspan, p)` in order to make use of a problem-specific struct for representing `W`. Just as with `Wfact` and `Wfact_t`, the custom struct is stored in `f.f1.jac_prototype`, while `f.jac_prototype` contains its [default value](https://github.com/SciML/SciMLBase.jl/blob/7f81097a492ab1707209530627a494bfb10c90c5/src/scimlfunctions.jl#L530) of `nothing`. When the algorithm cache is being built, `build_J_W` only uses a custom struct for representing `W` if [`f.jac_prototype !== nothing`](https://github.com/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/blob/3a9b6dc35e3ed19ddda4801cc5c791bf8771f956/src/derivative_utils.jl#L606), so it ignores the custom `jac_prototype` when the problem is specified as above.

These issues can be fixed as follows:
```
import SciMLBase: SplitFunction
function SplitFunction{iip}(f1,f2; kwargs...) where iip
  f1 = ODEFunction(f1)
  f2 = ODEFunction{iip}(f2)
  SplitFunction{iip,RECOMPILE_BY_DEFAULT}(f1,f2; kwargs...,
                                          Wfact = f1.Wfact,
                                          Wfact_t = f1.Wfact_t,
                                          jac_prototype = f1.jac_prototype,
  )
end
```
However, this solution causes custom values of `Wfact`, `Wfact_t`, and `jac_prototype` to be stored in two places for split ODE problems (in both `f` and `f.f1`). An alternative approach could be to make getter functions for `Wfact`, `Wfact_t`, and `jac_prototype`, and to use those functions in `calc_W!` and `build_J_W` instead of directly accessing the fields of `f`.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/issues/1510/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/issues/1510/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null},"comment":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/issues/comments/1094069376","html_url":"https://github.com/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/issues/1510#issuecomment-1094069376","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/issues/1510","id":1094069376,"node_id":"IC_kwDOBEVPe85BNiyA","user":{"login":"danielwe","id":5809017,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU4MDkwMTc=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5809017?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/danielwe","html_url":"https://github.com/danielwe","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/danielwe/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/danielwe/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/danielwe/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/danielwe/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/danielwe/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/danielwe/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/danielwe/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/danielwe/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/danielwe/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2022-04-09T15:35:56Z","updated_at":"2022-04-09T15:35:56Z","author_as